{
  "texts": [
    "In the second subsection, we focus on one of the most studied social dynamics involving groups, namely complex contagion.",
    "Here, we show that a low intra-order hyperedge overlap leads to explosive transitions characterized by a bistable region, where both an active and an absorbent state coexist.",
    "Conversely, hypergraphs with an intra-order hyperedge overlap larger than a critical value can only exhibit continuous transitions.",
    "To show that these results extend beyond complex spreading to other dynamics, in the third subsection we study synchronization of coupled dynamical systems with higher-order interactions.",
    "Synchronization is a collective behavior that emerges in various social and biological complex systems."
  ]
}